<TITLE> Zillur calls for upholding democratic ideals </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 15 (bdnews24.com) - Zillur Rahman is spending his first day at the presidential secretariat at the Bangabhaban Sunday after having been sworn in as the president Feb.12. On arrival at the Bangabhaban after 10:30am, president Rahman went to the Darbar Hall and urged the assembled officials and employees present to work in unison to uphold the democratic ideals for a prosperous and happy nation. "Our national parliament will be the focal centre for discussing all national issues. We have to maintain our tolerance, practice democracy all the way and respect others," said the president. "You must discharge your duties most impartially, upholding the image and reputation of this institution, so that no one can ever raise question our integrity and honour." A smart contingent of the President's Guard Regiment gave Rahman a guard of honour as he reached Bangabhaban from his residence at Ivy Tower in Gulshan. Md Sirajul Islam, secretary to the president's office, greeted the president with flowersin presence of the president's military secretary Md Ruhul Amin, press secretary Abdul Awal and other officials. Abul Kalam Azad, deputy press secretary to the president, told bdnews24.com, "The honourable president is present in his Bangabhaban office." Zillur expressed hope that independence leader Sheikh Mujibur Rahman's daughter prime minister Sheikh Hasina and her government would succeed in transforming Bangladesh into a prosperous country. b
